Located on the first floor of a private house featuring private access to the entire apartment including kitchen, bathroom, dining area, living room, 3 bedrooms.

You have 100% private access to the entire apartment (everything in the pictures). You do not have to share the space with anyone.

* Door to stairway to backyard (door next to dining table, do not open) access is prohibited unless there is an emergency (fire, etc), DO NOT OPEN.

I will be unavailable to answer phone calls but feel free to contact Emily (co-host) if there is anything you need.
The best way to contact us is through the Airbnb message channel as we usually respond in minutes. You can also text message, or call Emily.

Flushing is a neighborhood in the New York City borough of Queens. While much of the neighborhood is residential, Downtown Flushing, centered on the northern end of Main Street in Queens, is a large commercial and retail area and is the fourth largest central business district in New York City.

Flushing's diversity is reflected by the numerous ethnic groups that reside there, including people of Asian, Hispanic, Middle Eastern, European, and African American ancestry. It is part of the Fifth Congressional District, which encompasses the entire northeastern shore of Queens County, and extends into neighboring Nassau County. Flushing is served by five railroad stations on the Long Island Rail Road Port Washington Branch, as well as the New York City Subway's 7 Flushing Line, which has its terminus at Main Street. The intersection of Main Street and Roosevelt Avenue is the third busiest intersection in New York City, behind Times and Herald Squares.

• Parking space in front of house. Please let me know in advance if you need to use the parking space so I can leave it empty.
• Walking distance to buses. 
• 10 mins drive to Main Street Flushing.
• 8 mins drive to LaGuardia airport and 15 mins drive to JFK airport.
• 30 mins drive to Manhattan.
• 1 hour via public transit to Manhattan.

The neighbor sometimes plays music.

I recommend using your favorite map apps to check traveling directions and the MTA transit website for bus/train schedules and other information.

If you have any questions or concerns, please send me a message first before booking.

The home is equipped with a video doorbell for security.

hosts.about:
Hi! My name is Emily and I live in Flushing, New York for most of my life and I am very excited to be able to host people from all over the world as an Airbnb Super Host! I am a Software Engineer, so it's not a surprise that I am into new gadgets and technology. I am currently very interested in smart homes and home automation. In my spare time I practice pilates. I also have an interest in crafts, home decor and improvement so sometimes I spend hours browsing on pinterest.
I am an avid learner and believe that there is always room to improve, learn new things and look at life in different perspectives. I'm especially fond of reading stories on Humans of New York.

I have a deep love for animal and have several furry family members of my own. But don't worry, they won't be in your space!

Hi, I'm Joyce. I lived in the Queens Flushing area for over 20 years and watched the city evolve into what it is today. My hobbies are cooking and gardening. In my free time, I take care of my grandchildren. 

I'm excited to be sharing my beautiful home where I lived at for almost 15 years with you!

review.comments:
This is a fantastic place to stay. A very clean and modern house, with an added bonus of having a driveway to park a car, which come in very handy for me. 

Emily was a fantastic host, with great communication before, during and after my stay. She even left supplies in the house for when I arrived, which was greatly appreciated. Emily was very helpful answering any questions I had. It was a very relaxing stay, and New York is only 20 minutes away by train, with local buses running directly to flushing Main Street station not far from the house. 

Would definitely recommend, and would return again!
